{
  "page": "Escutcheon",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"floatright\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Night%27s_Watch.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Night&#39;s Watch.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/70px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png\" width=\"70\" height=\"77\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/105px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/140px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png 2x\" /></a></div><p>An <b>escutcheon</b> is the shield-shaped surface normally used to display the heraldic design of a <a href=\"/index.php/Coat_of_arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coat of arms\">coat of arms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Most of the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Houses_of_Westeros\" title=\"Houses of Westeros\">noble houses</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> use <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heater_shield\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Heater shield\">\"heater\" shield</a>-shaped escutcheons for their coats of arms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> However, in <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a> round shields are preferred, and thus round-shaped coats of arms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Escutcheon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Knighthood</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Feudalism\" title=\"Feudalism\">Feudalism</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Heraldry\" title=\"Heraldry\">Heraldry</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Escutcheon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escutcheon_(heraldry)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Escutcheon (heraldry)\">Wikipedia: Escutcheon (heraldry)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_29\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 29\">Chapter 29</a>, The Reaver.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_48\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 48\">Chapter 48</a>, Jaime I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_38\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 38\">Chapter 38</a>, Tyrion V.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403152339\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.020 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.023 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 281/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8650/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1041/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 66/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1671/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   13.781      1 -total\n 77.80%   10.722      3 Template:Ref\n 52.50%    7.235      3 Template:Ref/core\n 20.00%    2.757      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:2400-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403152339 and revision id 211698\n -->\n",
